'''Nicolaas Johannes "Stokkies" Hanekom''' (born 17 May 1989) is a South African [[rugby union]] player, currently playing with the {{Rut Golden Lions}}.<ref name="SARU Player Profile Stokkies Hanekom">{{cite web | work=sarugby.net | url=http://www.sarugby.net/playerprofile.aspx?id=46154 | title=SARU Player Profile Stokkies Hanekom | work=South African Rugby Union | accessdate=25 April 2013}}</ref> His regular position is outside centre.

==Career==
As a pupil at [[Paarl Gimnasium]], he started his career playing for local team {{Rut Western Province}} at youth level, playing for their Under-19 team in 2008 and their Under-21 team in 2009 and 2010.

In 2009, he was included in the [[South Africa national under-20 rugby union team|S.A. Under-20]] team for the [[2009 IRB Junior World Championship]].<ref name="2009 IRB Junior World Championships Semi-Finals">{{cite web | work=irb.com | url=http://www.irb.com/jwc/matches/match=10870/index.html | title=2009 IRB Junior World Championships Semi-Finals | accessdate=7 November 2011}}</ref>

He had a short spell for {{Rut Griquas}} during the [[2011 Vodacom Cup]] tournament, but failed to make a first class appearance, despite twice being named on the bench. He was then included in the {{Rut Western Province}} squad for the [[2011 Currie Cup Premier Division#Compulsory Friendlies|compulsory friendlies]] prior to the 
[[2011 Currie Cup Premier Division]] season, but failed to break into the team.

He moved to {{Rut SWD Eagles}} for the [[2012 Currie Cup First Division]] season, starting all fourteen games that season.

At the start of 2013, he joined the {{Rut Lions}}<ref name="Nog Maties Leeus toe">{{cite web | url=http://www.suparugby.com/pages/Default.asp?More=%20-%208%20November%202012&FeatureID=20038&SectionID=49 | title=Nog Maties Leeus toe | date=8 Nov 2012 | publisher=SupaRugby | accessdate=8 Nov 2012 | language=Afrikaans}}</ref> and was included in their squad for the 2013 Lions Challenge Series, as well as the {{Rut Golden Lions}}' [[2013 Vodacom Cup]] squad.

